In this press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sean Spicer discussed a range of topics. He mentioned that President Trump is monitoring severe weather in Louisiana and has approved additional public assistance for three counties in Mississippi. Spicer also highlighted the President's recent meetings with military leaders, county sheriffs, and veterans advocates. He mentioned the President's commitment to reforming the Department of Veterans Affairs and improving healthcare access for veterans. Spicer also mentioned the President's recent decision to appoint Betsy DeVos as Secretary of Education and his intention to repeal and replace the Affordable Care Act. He discussed the ongoing legal battle over the travel ban executive order and the President's commitment to keeping the country safe. Spicer also mentioned upcoming meetings with foreign leaders, including Prime Minister Rajoy of Spain and President Erdogan of Turkey. Finally, he touched on the recent suicide bombing in Kabul and the President's commitment to supporting Afghanistan.